ufficient depth and deep pencil beams do not observe enough galaxies in the\nrequisite luminosity and redshift bins. Also, intensity mapping is often the\nmost efficient way to measure the power spectrum shape, depending on the\ndetails of the luminosity function and the telescope aperture.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jul 2014 00:10:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
