adictions are present. And finally,\nthat a properly stated Vibrating Rays Theory is compatible with all known\nexperiments on electromagnetism and light propagation. In the present work we\nwill (1) explain how VRT should be interpreted, and why past experiments were\nmisinterpreted, (2) show the characteristics of VRT that are present in\nspacecraft anomalies, (3) give a possible theoretical model (including the\npossible presence of longitudinal waves), and (4) describe results in an\nongoing experiment designed to distinguish between VRT and SRT models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Jul 2014 19:09:50 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Mon, 26 Aug 2019 17:39:46 GMT"},{"version":"v11","created":"Thu, 21 Nov 2019 18:21:30 GMT"},{"version":"v12","created":"Fri, 29 Nov 2019 20:30:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 21 Jul 2014 18:45:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 1 Sep 2014 23:52:44 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 10 Sep 2014 19:05:10 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 2 Oct 2015 15:39:07 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 23 Mar 2016 14:54:47 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 12 Jul 2016 21:17:45 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2016 08:23:35 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Thu, 8 Aug 2019 11:08:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-03"}
